column5: The Ranch in Baudette is now Alice's Restaurant. Stopped there Saturday and it was clean, fast and good food. Inside is re-done nicely.

Did they have a half a ton of garbage and did they prosecute you with 27 8 x 10 color glossy photographs with circles and arrows and a paragraph on the back of each one explaining how it was to be used as evidence against you?
AND... did they ask "Son, have you ever been arrested?SERIOUSLY, do they have a "duty free" shop in Baudette / Rainy River to purchase booze?
Yea Jimi, there is duty free in Baudette.
Ya know, you can get anything you want at Alice's Restaurant...exceptin' Alice.
I was assigned to the Group W bench with mother rapers! And Mushmouth!
I cannot believe how good the pancakes taste there, they are soooo good. Our whole group pigged out on those things, year after year.

Whoa, I guess I missed this, I was up near Nakina when this post was active. I was just getting ready to ask if the place had reopened, glad to see this. I noticed the Baudette Oktoberfest is now in the middle of the week, I wonder why, as it used to be on a weekend the last time I attended. Bill Krejca
